entries.title: Jetstar plane forced to make an emergency landing in Japan after receiving bomb threat
entries.description: A Jetstar plane with 149 passengers onboard has been forced to make an emergency landing in central Japan after receiving a bomb threat.

entries.title: Death toll rises to six as deadly storm smashes into California
entries.description: Gary Yules, 72, Mei Keng Lam, 57, Katherine 'Kathy' Martinez, 61, Steven Sampson, 45, Aeon 'Goldie' Tocchini, 2, and a 19-year-old Solano County woman have lost their lives.

entries.title: Versace the parrot scares away would-be home intruders in Mickleham
entries.description: The blue and yellow macaw named Versace was in her cage in the Kavanagh's family home in Mickleham, north of Melbourne, while they celebrated New Years Eve.

entries.title: Dragon Rachel Elnaugh, who said Chris Whitty 'will hang' has set up safe haven for anti-vaxxers
entries.description: Former Dragon's Den star Rachel Elnaugh, 58, has raised nearly £1million with a group called Phoenix Rose to buy 70 acres of Derbyshire forest for a 'safe haven' for anti-vaxxers.

entries.title: Camilla did not leak details of her first meeting with William to the press, royal sources claim
entries.description: In new autobiography Spare, Prince Harry makes a series of bombshell revelations, including the claim that Camilla gave 'pinpoint accurate details' to the press about the first time she met the heir.

entries.title: King Charles is determined to mend the rift between Harry and Royal Family
entries.description: King Charles is said to be willing to take the Duke of Sussex's call and heal the rift in the hopes that he will attend his Coronation on May 6, Palace insiders say.

entries.title: Outraged Celine Dion fans protest outside offices Rolling Stone after music mag omitted from top 200
entries.description: Fans of Celine Dion gathered outside the New York City offices of Rolling Stone Magazine to protest the singer's exclusion from magazine's list of The 200 Greatest Singers of All Time.

entries.title: Sydney homeowner finds alarming discovery on their door step as termites swarm house
entries.description: The Sydney homeowner awoke to find 'thousands' of insects infesting their front doormat on Monday morning before posting a photo to social media asking people to help identify the bugs.

entries.title: Prince Harry sensationally claims he wasn't actually William's best man at 2011 wedding
entries.description: The Duke revealed his deeply personal rift with his older sibling, the Prince of Wales, meant 'Willy didn't want me giving a best man's speech' at his 2011 wedding, according to his bombshell memoir.

entries.title: Australia weather: When the rain will stop as east coast drenched and ex-tropical cyclone floods WA
entries.description: In Sydney and up the east coast into Queensland, more wild weather continues on Saturday but respite is in sight, with rain clearing Sunday into Monday.

entries.title: 'Aussie Cossack' quizzed by cops over Ukrainian ambassador harassment
entries.description: Simeon Boikov prank-called Vasyl Myroshnychenko live on his YouTube show on Thursday, broadcasting the diplomat's number to his 150,000 followers.

entries.title: Trainee policeman whose hearing aids turned police sirens into 'torture' wins discrimination claim
entries.description: Probationer officer Shafi Karim was sacked from the Met after his poor hearing led to fears that he was unsafe on the job, an employment tribunal heard.

entries.title: Parents of pregnant woman murdered in Northern Ireland fear killer may have left the country
entries.description: Ms McNally, who was 15 weeks pregnant, was stabbed in her home in the Silverwood Green area of Lurgan on December 18. Police initially arrested two men aged 32 but neither were charged

entries.title: Cyber attackers demand £15 million from British schools they hacked over the Christmas holidays
entries.description: Some teachers returning to work this week were left unable to log in to their computers after an attack by an online gang on the IT systems of at least 16 schools in Britain.

entries.title: Police hunt burglar using e-fit which looks uncannily like Take That superstar Gary Barlow
entries.description: A man who broke into a home in Deal, Kent in the early hours of December 17. The homeowners were woken up by the raid and confronted the burglar.

entries.title: Great idea, sir: Woke school bans teachers from using sarcasm in the classroom
entries.description: Skegness Academy in Lincolnshire stopped the use of irony to convey contempt as part of a 'guide to support staff'.

entries.title: Man, 34, is charged with terrorism after he 'deliberately destroyed solar energy plant'
entries.description: Mohammad Mesmarian, 34, was arrested for allegedly ramming his Toyota Camry into a Las Vegas solar energy generator pit and setting it on fire. He reportedly did so 'for the future.'

entries.title: South Beach local finds deadly blue ring octopus lurking inside her bathers
entries.description: A beachgoer has survived a deadly encounter with the infamous blue ringed octopus, finding one lodged inside of her bathers after going for a swim.

entries.title: Biggenden shed fire: Travel blogger and OnlyFans creator Kristen Olsen, 24, charged with murder
entries.description: Kristen Olsen, 24, has been charged with two counts of murder and one count of arson after the bodies of Todd Mooney, 54, and his daughter Kirra, 10, were found in a burned down shed in December.

entries.title: Trans male swimmer Iszac Henig struggles to go head-to-head against men after transitioning
entries.description: Henig, 21, has begun swimming for the Yale men's team after placing as an All-American on the women's team the previous year.

entries.title: Grammy-winning engineer killed by cops in Nashville after allegedly holding family hostage
entries.description: Mark Capps, 54, was fatally shot at his Nashville home by police SWAT team around 2pm Thursday after holding his wife Tara Solomon Capps, 60, and 23-year-old stepdaughter hostage.

entries.title: JAN MOIR: As Prince faces more fawning interviewers, the 20 questions our interrogator would ask...
entries.description: JAN MOIR: Over the next few days, Prince Harry will subject himself to a round of television interviews to support his bombshell autobiography, Spare. Will the broadcasts get to the heart of royal matters?

entries.title: Kristi Noem's office tears into DeSantis on abortion
entries.description: South Dakota Gov. Kristi Noem's communications director ripped into Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis suggesting the Republican rising star's abortion stance was too liberal.

entries.title: ANDREW NEIL: Harry's Taliban killing claim is a blunder his reputation will never recover from
entries.description: ANDREW NEIL: The boast that Prince Harry killed 25 Taliban while serving as an Army helicopter pilot in Afghanistan will do him the most long-term damage by far. I doubt he will recover from it.

entries.title: What turned the son of a chess champion and a Luton dinner lady into the world's most toxic man?
entries.description: Amid the fripperies on show at Andrew Tate's palatial Romanian mountainside villa, a humble chess board is a stark reminder of the past he has left behind.

entries.title: ROBERT HARDMAN visits the Alpine resorts forced to close runs or even shut down entirely
entries.description: ROBERT HARDMAN: The sell-out crowd of 25,000 at the bottom of the hill will be authentic enough, as will the dangers for the athletes. If the cameras pan back they will see a narrow white stripe.

entries.title: Labor government slammed for $150,000 spending spree on functions and hospitality in three months
entries.description: The Albanese government has spent more than $150,000 in three months on functions and hospitality for the purpose of 'introducing themselves' between June and August.

entries.title: Prince Harry was allowed to miss drugs test and leave UK RAF base after it was put in lockdown
entries.description: RAF Wittisham in Suffolk was reportedly secured by armed guards in May 2011 before all cadets, junior and senior, were ordered to give urine samples.

entries.title: Idaho State Police begin clearing Moscow rental home where students were murdered
entries.description: Idaho State Police began clearing the Moscow home where four University of Idaho students were stabbed to death - a day after their alleged killer was formally charged.
